COMBINED HR POLICY DOCUMENT – SAMPLE (For AI HR Assistant Agent)

1. LEAVE POLICY
1.1 Annual Leave
Employees are entitled to 20 days of paid annual leave per calendar year.
Maximum 5 unused days can be carried forward.

1.2 Sick Leave
Employees receive 12 paid sick leaves per year.
Medical certificate required if sick leave exceeds 2 days.

1.3 Casual Leave
Employees are eligible for 7 casual leaves per year.

1.4 Maternity / Paternity Leave
Maternity: 26 weeks for eligible employees.
Paternity: 15 days.

1.5 Leave Application
All leave requests must be submitted through the HR Portal at least 7 days in advance.

----------------------------------------------------------------

2. BENEFITS & COMPENSATION
2.1 Health Insurance
Covers employee + spouse + 2 children under group policy.

2.2 Provident Fund (PF)
Employer contributes 12% of basic salary.

2.3 Gratuity
Applicable after completing 5+ years of continuous service.

2.4 Reimbursements
Travel, food, and client-meeting costs reimbursed upon receipt submission.

----------------------------------------------------------------

3. CODE OF CONDUCT
3.1 Professional Behavior
All employees must maintain professionalism and integrity.

3.2 Anti-Harassment Policy
Zero tolerance for workplace harassment.

3.3 Confidentiality
No employee shall disclose internal or client data without authorization.

----------------------------------------------------------------

4. WORKING HOURS & ATTENDANCE
4.1 General Working Hours
Employees must complete 8 hours/day (flexible shifts allowed).

4.2 Work from Home Policy
Employees may avail up to 40% remote work monthly.

4.3 Attendance Regularization
Must be applied within 48 hours if missed punch.

----------------------------------------------------------------

5. PERFORMANCE & APPRAISAL
5.1 Appraisal Cycle
Annual appraisal conducted during Jan–Feb.

5.2 Promotion Criteria
Based on performance, skill growth, and business needs.

----------------------------------------------------------------

6. GRIEVANCE REDRESSAL
6.1 Contact
Employees can raise grievances via hr@company.com.

6.2 Response Time
HR must acknowledge grievances within 48 hours and resolve within 10 working days.

----------------------------------------------------------------

7. TERMINATION & NOTICE
7.1 Notice Period
Standard notice period: 30 days or salary in lieu.

7.2 Misconduct
Company may terminate without notice in case of proven misconduct.
